Igbo traders at Odunade market in Orile, Lagos, are currently holding a protest against paying any fee that is being ordered by Iya Loja. Iya Loja are chair lady of markets in Yorubaland. The protesters, who were majorly men came out in large numbers carrying placards with inscriptions such as ‘We are pleading on our government to come to our aid. A big no to Iya Loja. “ Watch video below: Igbo traders at Odunade market in Lagos stage protest against paying money to their women market leader otherwise known as Iya Oloja…. A post shared by  Lindaikejiblog (@lindaikejiblogofficial) on Jan 27, 2020 at 6:37am PST Source